WEBVTT

1
00:00:05.133 --> 00:00:08.171
Looks like they're all asleep.
Maybe I should sneak out of here.

2
00:00:08.470 --> 00:00:11.747
No. Why don't you stay for breakfast.

3
00:00:12.516 --> 00:00:14.234
How do you like your eggs?

4
00:00:14.518 --> 00:00:17.078
-What about your sisters?
-What about them?

5
00:00:17.396 --> 00:00:19.546
PAIGE: Aah!
RICHARD: Whoa!

6
00:00:20.440 --> 00:00:23.273
Oh. sorry. You okay?

7
00:00:23.986 --> 00:00:26.978
-What are you doing?
-Trying to fix the garbage disposal.

8
00:00:27.281 --> 00:00:30.239
-What are you doing?
-Messing around.

9
00:00:30.575 --> 00:00:31.974
Oh. Uh-huh.

10
00:00:32.244 --> 00:00:34.554
Hey. sorry. I should have told you
I was here.

11
00:00:34.871 --> 00:00:39.502
No. don't be silly. Paige is a big girl.
She can hang out all she wants to.

12
00:00:39.918 --> 00:00:41.909
Not that she does a lot. I mean...

13
00:00:42.212 --> 00:00:44.168
-You can stop now.
-Right.

14
00:00:44.463 --> 00:00:46.101
Hey. you mind if I take a look?

15
00:00:46.674 --> 00:00:47.994
Sure. go ahead.

16
00:00:48.718 --> 00:00:50.311
Okay.

17
00:00:51.178 --> 00:00:53.089
[DISPOSAL GRINDING]

18
00:00:54.056 --> 00:00:55.729
What's wrong with the disposal
anyway?

19
00:00:55.975 --> 00:00:58.410
Not disposing. washer not washing.
Cable not cabling.

20
00:00:58.686 --> 00:01:01.280
PAIGE: Don't forget the sink upstairs.
-It's next on my list.

21
00:01:01.606 --> 00:01:04.678
-Sounds like fun.
-That's my life. actually. All about fun.

22
00:01:11.574 --> 00:01:14.885
-There you go. It's as good as new.
-He's handy to have around.

23
00:01:15.202 --> 00:01:17.557
Yeah. I thought you didn't use
magic anymore.

24
00:01:17.872 --> 00:01:21.308
Just once in a while. for little things.
Want me to fix the washer?

25
00:01:21.667 --> 00:01:22.987
-Yes.
-No.

26
00:01:23.210 --> 00:01:25.520
Can you guys help me pick out
some earrings?

27
00:01:26.964 --> 00:01:29.001
Hi. I didn't know you were here.

28
00:01:29.675 --> 00:01:32.269
Hey. yeah. We got in late last night.

29
00:01:32.929 --> 00:01:35.284
-I see.
-He fixed the garbage disposal.

30
00:01:35.598 --> 00:01:37.589
-Really?
-Mm-hm. Magically.

31
00:01:38.601 --> 00:01:40.160
Really?

32
00:01:43.981 --> 00:01:46.131
Can you help me with my earrings
out here. please?

33
00:01:47.276 --> 00:01:48.596
Sure.

34
00:01:49.904 --> 00:01:51.736
Excuse me.

35
00:01:53.699 --> 00:01:56.930
So how do you like your eggs.
scrambled or over easy?

36
00:01:58.162 --> 00:02:00.836
Okay. listen. was that weird?

37
00:02:01.123 --> 00:02:02.477
Why are you so dressed up?

38
00:02:02.708 --> 00:02:05.222
Because I have a date with Jason.
but that's besides the point.

39
00:02:05.544 --> 00:02:08.504
Didn't Richard lose it the last time
he used magic? I mean. really lose it?

40
00:02:08.838 --> 00:02:11.352
Uh. I can assure you that he stayed
in complete control

41
00:02:11.633 --> 00:02:13.306
over the garbage disposal.

42
00:02:14.177 --> 00:02:16.137
It's 7:00 in the morning.
how can you have a date?

43
00:02:16.388 --> 00:02:18.504
Because it's 7 here.
but it's evening in Hong Kong.

44
00:02:19.140 --> 00:02:21.734
Okay. so you're not concerned
about Richard using magic?

45
00:02:22.060 --> 00:02:25.655
Yeah. I am. but I'm more concerned
with Paige being really pissed off

46
00:02:25.981 --> 00:02:27.972
because we butted into
her business again.

47
00:02:28.233 --> 00:02:30.833
Yeah. I know. but we're sisters.
that's what we're supposed to do.

48
00:02:31.069 --> 00:02:34.744
Back to your date. I don't understand.
is Chris orbing you to Hong Kong?

49
00:02:35.115 --> 00:02:36.389
No. we're video conferencing.

50
00:02:36.616 --> 00:02:39.335
We just open our laptops
and there we are. in color.

51
00:02:39.661 --> 00:02:41.254
Mm-hm. In each other's laps.

52
00:02:41.538 --> 00:02:43.848
So do you think we should
talk to Paige about Richard?

53
00:02:44.165 --> 00:02:46.918
-We don't really know him.
-I know we don't.

54
00:02:47.210 --> 00:02:49.042
And neither does she.
That's the problem.

55
00:02:50.839 --> 00:02:54.070
-What. can't I worry?
-From afar. Yeah.

56
00:02:54.551 --> 00:02:57.703
Now. excuse me.
I have to go unclog a sink.

57
00:03:08.023 --> 00:03:10.776
Well. maybe a little magic
couldn't hurt.

58
00:03:20.285 --> 00:03:22.083
Help me!

59
00:03:32.839 --> 00:03:35.273
Okay. so watery lady
pops up from the sink.

60
00:03:35.549 --> 00:03:38.701
-You sure she's not a demon?
-I'm sure she needed help.

61
00:03:39.053 --> 00:03:40.773
-What else did she say?
PIPER: That was it.

62
00:03:40.888 --> 00:03:42.640
"Harding Park. pond." and poof!

63
00:03:43.641 --> 00:03:44.870
[WATER BUBBLING]

64
00:03:47.603 --> 00:03:49.002
Over there.

65
00:04:06.872 --> 00:04:09.546
They're coming! Take this.
it does not belong to them!

66
00:04:10.584 --> 00:04:12.177
[GASPS]

67
00:04:25.724 --> 00:04:27.681
[GRUNTING]

68
00:04:45.577 --> 00:04:47.250
I'm liking these odds.

69
00:04:51.750 --> 00:04:53.104
Wuss.

70
00:04:54.044 --> 00:04:55.193
LADY OF THE LAKE:
The sword.

71
00:04:56.797 --> 00:04:58.708
The sword is...

72
00:05:01.217 --> 00:05:03.094
Where'd she go?
What did she say?

73
00:05:03.344 --> 00:05:07.178
Uh. she said something
about the sword. Where is it?

74
00:05:07.807 --> 00:05:09.764
It's in the stone.

75
00:05:16.316 --> 00:05:18.353
The sword in the stone?

76
00:05:18.651 --> 00:05:21.803
Oh. you gotta be kidding me. right?

77
00:07:08.802 --> 00:07:10.759
Okay. could you maybe
miss the table?

78
00:07:11.013 --> 00:07:13.766
I'm sorry. I've never orbed anything
that heavy before.

79
00:07:14.057 --> 00:07:17.129
-Or that historic.
-Is that glowing?

80
00:07:17.436 --> 00:07:20.030
No. it's the sunroom.
there's a lot of light.

81
00:07:20.355 --> 00:07:22.915
What part of this aren't you getting?
Sword. stone. lady in lake.

82
00:07:23.150 --> 00:07:24.379
It was a pond.

83
00:07:25.611 --> 00:07:28.410
-You think she's from Avalon?
-Yeah. I think she was flushed out

84
00:07:28.697 --> 00:07:31.689
by whoever's after Excalibur.
The maker of kings.

85
00:07:31.992 --> 00:07:35.872
Look. we're not talking about Camelot.
right. because that's not real.

86
00:07:36.246 --> 00:07:38.966
You never believed in King Arthur
and the Knights of the Round Table?

87
00:07:39.291 --> 00:07:42.647
Yes. I did. when I was 7.
And then I grew up.

88
00:07:43.211 --> 00:07:45.646
Yeah. you grew up to be a witch

89
00:07:45.923 --> 00:07:47.914
that fights demons
and silly-looking dragons.

90
00:07:48.216 --> 00:07:50.492
-That's different. that's real.
-And this isn't real?

91
00:07:50.802 --> 00:07:53.475
-What is real are those hooded freaks.
-Who are not gonna give up

92
00:07:53.763 --> 00:07:55.883
-now that the sword's in the open.
-How do you know?

93
00:07:56.140 --> 00:07:59.451
Whoever has Excalibur
is unstoppable.

94
00:08:02.813 --> 00:08:05.248
Okay. there's definitely nothing
in the <i>Book.</i>

95
00:08:05.524 --> 00:08:07.754
Oh. hi. How you doing?

96
00:08:08.986 --> 00:08:10.897
Phoebe. please put a stop
to this nonsense.

97
00:08:11.197 --> 00:08:13.175
-Didn't realise you were here.
PAIGE: That's okay.

98
00:08:13.199 --> 00:08:14.678
You can talk freely in front of him.

99
00:08:14.909 --> 00:08:17.105
Lord knows.
you've been through enough.

100
00:08:18.246 --> 00:08:20.840
-No. not really.
-Phoebe.

101
00:08:21.791 --> 00:08:23.748
Look. I should probably go.

102
00:08:24.460 --> 00:08:27.054
Don't be ridiculous. You're great.

103
00:08:27.380 --> 00:08:29.690
Okay. anyway. <i>Book.</i> Excalibur...?

104
00:08:30.007 --> 00:08:31.202
Yeah. nothing. <i>nada.</i>

105
00:08:31.467 --> 00:08:32.821
-Really?
-Told you.

106
00:08:33.094 --> 00:08:36.212
You know. hey. maybe it's been out
of circulation since ye olden days.

107
00:08:36.514 --> 00:08:38.983
and maybe no Halliwell has ever
come across it before.

108
00:08:39.308 --> 00:08:41.902
Well. we have run across these guys.
executioner demons.

109
00:08:42.353 --> 00:08:45.584
-lower-level badasses for hire.
-Who hired them?

110
00:08:45.898 --> 00:08:48.253
This higher-level badass.

111
00:08:48.776 --> 00:08:51.211
"A power-mad paladin
of destruction."

112
00:08:52.113 --> 00:08:55.743
Huh. Maybe... You know. maybe we
should just kind of hang out later.

113
00:08:56.075 --> 00:08:59.067
Yeah. Okay. Bye.

114
00:08:59.412 --> 00:09:00.891
Bye.

115
00:09:03.833 --> 00:09:04.948
[MOUTHS]
<i>I don't know.</i>

116
00:09:05.626 --> 00:09:10.018
-Be careful with all this.
-Always. I had...

117
00:09:11.132 --> 00:09:14.443
-...a really good time last night.
-Me too.

118
00:09:15.595 --> 00:09:17.107
What?

119
00:09:17.345 --> 00:09:21.179
Uh. I just don't think your sisters
like me very much.

120
00:09:21.558 --> 00:09:23.595
-No. that's not true.
-Really?

121
00:09:23.852 --> 00:09:27.368
Okay. maybe they're just doing
the overprotective sister thing.

122
00:09:28.106 --> 00:09:29.858
Mmm. Well. that's a good thing.

123
00:09:30.108 --> 00:09:33.260
Because I don't want anything
to happen to you.

124
00:09:33.570 --> 00:09:34.640
Don't worry.

125
00:09:40.535 --> 00:09:42.412
So he's an upper-level demon.
which means

126
00:09:42.662 --> 00:09:45.973
you should be able to make
a vanquishing potion.

127
00:09:46.291 --> 00:09:49.124
Okay. Wait. Me? Why me?

128
00:09:49.419 --> 00:09:52.775
Because. hello. I have a few
hundred things to do

129
00:09:53.089 --> 00:09:55.049
around here. in addition
to raising a small child.

130
00:09:55.300 --> 00:09:56.938
I know. you have so much to do.

131
00:09:57.177 --> 00:09:59.691
You're my hero. But I can't.
I have to go to work.

132
00:09:59.971 --> 00:10:02.247
I still don't have an assistant.
and I'm swamped.

133
00:10:02.515 --> 00:10:04.028
But... Phoebe!

134
00:10:06.436 --> 00:10:08.473
Paige. potion?

135
00:10:08.772 --> 00:10:11.924
Oh. I'm sorry. honey. the temp
agency's already got me a new job.

136
00:10:12.275 --> 00:10:14.585
But that hardly compares with...

137
00:10:14.861 --> 00:10:16.501
Come on. you know
there's a magical reason

138
00:10:16.738 --> 00:10:18.218
that I've had every one
of these jobs.

139
00:10:18.406 --> 00:10:20.204
and who am I to interfere
with destiny?

140
00:10:20.450 --> 00:10:23.806
Okay. so you want me
to add "babysit the sword"

141
00:10:24.120 --> 00:10:27.272
and "mix vanquishing potion"
to my never-ending to-do list.

142
00:10:27.624 --> 00:10:30.138
Look. the sword is stuck
in the stone. You know it. I know it.

143
00:10:30.418 --> 00:10:33.179
the bad guys know it. Nobody's gonna
get it out till King Arthur does.

144
00:10:33.463 --> 00:10:35.383
When that happens.
there'll be lots of fireworks.

145
00:10:35.632 --> 00:10:37.272
-When might that be?
-How should I know?

146
00:10:37.467 --> 00:10:39.424
Maybe a couple thousand years?

147
00:10:50.020 --> 00:10:52.489
Well. you can't blame a girl for trying.

148
00:10:58.904 --> 00:10:59.974
[DEMON GRUNTS]

149
00:11:00.197 --> 00:11:02.154
DARK KNIGHT:
Oh. but I do blame you.

150
00:11:02.449 --> 00:11:05.680
The sword is now locked in stone.
You promised me murderers.

151
00:11:05.995 --> 00:11:08.748
what you delivered
was cannon fodder for witches!

152
00:11:09.081 --> 00:11:10.754
Those weren't just witches.

153
00:11:11.000 --> 00:11:14.197
Tell me. demon. will your thick head
still spout excuses

154
00:11:14.503 --> 00:11:16.096
when it's cut from your neck?

155
00:11:16.380 --> 00:11:18.451
If the sword is
with the Charmed Ones.

156
00:11:18.716 --> 00:11:21.185
it means we need a better class
of executioners. that's all.

157
00:11:25.222 --> 00:11:26.974
And how much more
will this cost me?

158
00:11:27.766 --> 00:11:30.918
-The Charmed Ones are formidable.
-How much?

159
00:11:31.270 --> 00:11:32.943
To provide you
with more executioners

160
00:11:33.230 --> 00:11:36.700
and the training needed to drown the
Charmed Ones in their own blood...

161
00:11:40.654 --> 00:11:43.487
...a seat at the table.

162
00:11:47.494 --> 00:11:51.852
If your goal is to unite all evil under
the corrupted power of the sword.

163
00:11:52.207 --> 00:11:54.721
you could do far worse
than have me at your side.

164
00:12:00.799 --> 00:12:04.235
-Responses to last week's columns.
-How'd you get into my e-mail?

165
00:12:04.553 --> 00:12:07.272
Your e-mail account is maxed out.
so your fans are using ours.

166
00:12:07.889 --> 00:12:11.519
Oh. I'll tell you. Elise better find me
a new assistant because pretty soon

167
00:12:11.851 --> 00:12:15.367
she's gonna have to ask Phoebe
to take my foot out of her...

168
00:12:15.730 --> 00:12:17.164
[PHONE RINGS]

169
00:12:17.649 --> 00:12:20.209
Hello. Phoebe Halliwell.

170
00:12:20.485 --> 00:12:22.601
Oh. hey. Laura.

171
00:12:22.862 --> 00:12:24.614
I have that down...

172
00:12:26.032 --> 00:12:30.151
...for this morning. Oh. my God.
I missed it. I'm so sorry.

173
00:12:30.495 --> 00:12:32.486
No. of course I can reschedule.
Absolutely.

174
00:12:32.747 --> 00:12:33.896
[PAIGE CLEARS THROAT]

175
00:12:35.375 --> 00:12:39.448
Actually. Laura. can I call you back
when I have my book in front of me?

176
00:12:39.796 --> 00:12:43.710
Okay. great. I'm so sorry.
Thanks. Bye.

177
00:12:44.092 --> 00:12:47.130
Hi. I thought you had
a new temp job today.

178
00:12:47.470 --> 00:12:49.666
-I do.
-Why aren't you there?

179
00:12:50.265 --> 00:12:51.824
Apparently I am.

180
00:12:53.101 --> 00:12:55.536
-What? Here?
-Yep.

181
00:12:55.812 --> 00:12:58.008
-As my assistant?
-Well. I think I'd prefer

182
00:12:58.273 --> 00:12:59.593
to be called your desk manager.

183
00:12:59.816 --> 00:13:02.934
Wait. but I thought you get all
of your temp jobs for divine reasons.

184
00:13:03.278 --> 00:13:04.348
Usually I do.

185
00:13:04.570 --> 00:13:06.925
Yeah. but I don't need divine help.
I need filing

186
00:13:07.198 --> 00:13:09.474
and faxing
and desk-management help.

187
00:13:09.784 --> 00:13:12.776
I'm your girl. I really am.
We'll just. you know. see if

188
00:13:13.079 --> 00:13:15.309
the divine stuff kind of appears later.
It usually does.

189
00:13:15.915 --> 00:13:19.465
Yeah. but I can't tell you what to do.
I mean. how weird is that?

190
00:13:19.836 --> 00:13:21.474
Well. it's no weirder than usual.

191
00:13:21.754 --> 00:13:24.746
-Oh. I see.
-Just kidding. sort of.

192
00:13:25.049 --> 00:13:27.810
Listen. you get back to your column.
I will call Laura and reschedule.

193
00:13:28.052 --> 00:13:29.486
I will...

194
00:13:29.846 --> 00:13:32.360
...help stuff.

195
00:13:35.100 --> 00:13:36.818
[RATTLING]

196
00:13:45.611 --> 00:13:47.329
Perfect.

197
00:13:56.038 --> 00:13:57.312
[GROANS]

198
00:13:58.790 --> 00:14:00.588
DWARF:
Hey. lady!

199
00:14:04.838 --> 00:14:07.034
We could really use
an authority figure out there.

200
00:14:08.216 --> 00:14:10.287
-What are you doing here?
-What am I doing here?

201
00:14:10.552 --> 00:14:13.112
I'm getting pushed around!
I just lost my place in line.

202
00:14:13.430 --> 00:14:14.829
What line?

203
00:14:22.773 --> 00:14:24.923
What...? What's going on here?

204
00:14:30.155 --> 00:14:31.748
Never.

205
00:14:33.533 --> 00:14:35.922
-What is this?
DWARF: Natural selection.

206
00:14:36.203 --> 00:14:38.877
Naturally. I hope the sword
selects me to be king.

207
00:14:39.164 --> 00:14:41.075
Finally get a little respect around here.

208
00:14:41.375 --> 00:14:43.332
[LAUGHING]

209
00:14:46.588 --> 00:14:50.980
You people. you creatures. whatever.
You can't be here. You gotta go.

210
00:14:51.385 --> 00:14:53.899
We have a divine right to try our hand.

211
00:14:54.346 --> 00:14:56.064
-Ooh. wow.
DWARF: Yeah.

212
00:14:56.306 --> 00:14:57.944
Ten feet's pretty much the distance.

213
00:14:58.558 --> 00:15:00.355
Back of the line. please.

214
00:15:00.768 --> 00:15:01.838
Hoof it. sister!

215
00:15:02.103 --> 00:15:05.459
Chris! Chris. Get down here.

216
00:15:06.649 --> 00:15:08.606
-Where's Chris?
-Busy.

217
00:15:09.151 --> 00:15:10.630
DWARF:
Let's go.

218
00:15:10.903 --> 00:15:12.303
-What's going on?
-Busy with what?

219
00:15:12.572 --> 00:15:15.325
Other charges. I took him
off your account again.

220
00:15:15.616 --> 00:15:17.573
-Our account?
-You know what I mean.

221
00:15:19.912 --> 00:15:23.143
-Whoa. is that what I think it is?
PIPER: No. No. it's not.

222
00:15:23.457 --> 00:15:25.846
Okay. now look. you gotta get
all these people out of here

223
00:15:26.127 --> 00:15:27.959
because I can't do this right now.

224
00:15:28.254 --> 00:15:30.848
Hey. hey. hey! No cuts. buddy.

225
00:15:38.222 --> 00:15:39.860
Hey. how was the staff meeting?

226
00:15:40.099 --> 00:15:41.819
Endless. How's my new assistant
working out?

227
00:15:42.059 --> 00:15:44.972
Oh. she put a fire under the interns.
that's for sure.

228
00:15:45.271 --> 00:15:46.750
Really? Hmm.

229
00:15:47.940 --> 00:15:49.419
Okay. who can help me with that?

230
00:15:49.650 --> 00:15:53.200
Great. you got it. And what about
collating and cross-referencing?

231
00:15:53.529 --> 00:15:55.645
You. And so you would
have databasing.

232
00:15:55.907 --> 00:15:58.626
All right. great. You boys
have your marching orders.

233
00:15:58.910 --> 00:16:01.026
I will check back with you
in a couple hours.

234
00:16:04.832 --> 00:16:07.824
Wow. who works here?

235
00:16:08.169 --> 00:16:10.843
You do. Who rocks?
That would be me.

236
00:16:11.172 --> 00:16:13.322
By the end of the day.
we'll have a system in place

237
00:16:13.591 --> 00:16:16.060
that tracks your column ideas.
your columns written

238
00:16:16.344 --> 00:16:17.664
and your columns considered.

239
00:16:17.887 --> 00:16:20.879
plus a separate file for your questions.
comments and fan mail.

240
00:16:21.223 --> 00:16:23.419
-I can't believe it.
-Well. believe it because you.

241
00:16:23.684 --> 00:16:26.516
my dear. are never going to miss
anything again.

242
00:16:26.853 --> 00:16:28.366
-That's good.
-It is good news

243
00:16:28.605 --> 00:16:30.323
because you. my dear.
need to concentrate.

244
00:16:30.565 --> 00:16:31.999
Yes. I do.

245
00:16:32.233 --> 00:16:35.032
Yes. you do.
Starting with tomorrow's column.

246
00:16:35.362 --> 00:16:38.593
-I already wrote tomorrow's column.
-Yeah. you did.

247
00:16:40.617 --> 00:16:43.006
Uh. is there a problem with it?

248
00:16:43.286 --> 00:16:45.277
Well. I mean. I'm no expert.

249
00:16:45.580 --> 00:16:47.571
but I was just thinking
about this one question.

250
00:16:47.832 --> 00:16:50.904
Okay. the girl's family wants her
to break up with him

251
00:16:51.211 --> 00:16:52.690
because they think
he's an alcoholic.

252
00:16:52.921 --> 00:16:55.071
And absent of any proof.
you're telling her to end it.

253
00:16:55.382 --> 00:16:59.660
Well. you know. not really end it.
just slow it down a bit.

254
00:17:00.387 --> 00:17:03.903
Okay. but slowing it down
by not seeing each other is.

255
00:17:04.224 --> 00:17:05.623
in effect. ending it.

256
00:17:05.892 --> 00:17:08.122
I just think you should
keep your eyes open.

257
00:17:08.895 --> 00:17:10.568
Keep my eyes open?

258
00:17:10.855 --> 00:17:13.734
I mean. I think that she should keep
her eyes open.

259
00:17:14.025 --> 00:17:17.336
-You know what I mean.
-Yeah.

260
00:17:18.738 --> 00:17:22.572
-This column's about Richard. isn't it?
-No. it is not about Richard.

261
00:17:22.909 --> 00:17:24.263
Don't be ridiculous.

262
00:17:25.537 --> 00:17:28.893
You hate him. I can tell.
and what's worse. he can tell.

263
00:17:29.249 --> 00:17:32.321
Look. Paige. if you're sensing
anything from me. it's just concern.

264
00:17:32.669 --> 00:17:36.139
I'm concerned that you're falling
too fast for a guy you barely know.

265
00:17:38.341 --> 00:17:40.537
But. you know.
it's none of my business.

266
00:17:40.844 --> 00:17:44.155
You're right. It's not
any of your business.

267
00:17:46.349 --> 00:17:47.862
Right.

268
00:17:49.519 --> 00:17:51.270
Hey. Piper needs your help. now.

269
00:17:57.318 --> 00:17:58.717
[GRUNTING]

270
00:17:59.904 --> 00:18:00.904
[YELLS]

271
00:18:03.657 --> 00:18:05.250
Pest.

272
00:18:07.995 --> 00:18:09.713
Oh. my!

273
00:18:09.955 --> 00:18:13.107
-I was afraid this would happen.
-You could have mentioned that.

274
00:18:13.417 --> 00:18:15.806
-And they won't leave?
PIPER: Oh. no. No.

275
00:18:16.086 --> 00:18:19.044
-More show up every minute.
-But no bad guys yet. right?

276
00:18:19.340 --> 00:18:21.331
What is that stench?
What is that stench?

277
00:18:21.634 --> 00:18:24.274
We gotta get this thing out
of here. Leo refuses to orb it.

278
00:18:24.595 --> 00:18:26.955
The Lady of the Lake came to you.
I'm not messing with that.

279
00:18:27.264 --> 00:18:31.622
Oh. for God's sakes. if you
will not get rid of it. then I will!

280
00:18:37.942 --> 00:18:39.171
MAN:
Your Majesty.

281
00:18:41.111 --> 00:18:42.749
Wow.

282
00:18:46.158 --> 00:18:47.387
[WIND WHISTLING]

283
00:18:58.712 --> 00:19:01.226
I bet you didn't expect this
when you got up this morning.

284
00:19:01.548 --> 00:19:04.142
-I...
-The sword has chosen.

285
00:19:05.302 --> 00:19:07.452
You are the new savior.

286
00:19:07.721 --> 00:19:09.519
The champion of good.

287
00:19:09.765 --> 00:19:11.438
the master of Excalibur.

288
00:19:13.310 --> 00:19:16.301
-Welcome to your new destiny.
-Oh. crap.

289
00:19:18.982 --> 00:19:22.054
PHOEBE: Okay. let's go.
Nothing to see here anymore.

290
00:19:22.360 --> 00:19:25.079
-no more show. <i>adiós.</i> scram.
-Your Majesty. seriously.

291
00:19:25.363 --> 00:19:28.401
if you need anything. anything at all.
Castles built. suits of armor.

292
00:19:28.700 --> 00:19:31.010
you name it. I got connections.

293
00:19:34.706 --> 00:19:37.778
Is it just me. or does it still
smell like ogre in here?

294
00:19:38.084 --> 00:19:41.076
I'm telling you. guys.
this is all a big mistake.

295
00:19:42.672 --> 00:19:44.390
-Stop that.
-It's drawn to you.

296
00:19:44.632 --> 00:19:47.511
-just like you're drawn to it.
-Do I look like I'm drawn to it. pal?

297
00:19:47.844 --> 00:19:50.199
-You will be in time.
-No. I don't have time

298
00:19:50.471 --> 00:19:51.471
to play Queen Arthur.

299
00:19:52.140 --> 00:19:56.611
Oh. come on. Piper. have a little fun.
Don't you realise what this means?

300
00:19:57.020 --> 00:19:58.454
One more thing on my to-do list?

301
00:19:58.730 --> 00:20:01.563
No. it means you. my dear.
are the chosen one.

302
00:20:01.900 --> 00:20:04.619
the first in centuries to have
power over the sword.

303
00:20:04.903 --> 00:20:06.302
Tell her all about it. Merlin.

304
00:20:07.196 --> 00:20:10.951
Oh. actually. the name's Mordaunt.
Merlin was just a fairy tale.

305
00:20:11.326 --> 00:20:12.725
Ha!

306
00:20:13.161 --> 00:20:14.913
-But Camelot was not.
-Aha!

307
00:20:15.371 --> 00:20:17.521
And thanks to you. it can rise again.

308
00:20:17.832 --> 00:20:20.950
So. what are you. a wizard.
a sorcerer?

309
00:20:21.294 --> 00:20:24.525
Actually. I'm neither.
I'm just a humble teacher

310
00:20:24.839 --> 00:20:26.432
in service of the sword.

311
00:20:26.716 --> 00:20:28.753
And we must begin
instruction immediately.

312
00:20:29.052 --> 00:20:30.451
before your enemy attacks.

313
00:20:30.720 --> 00:20:32.040
-The Dark Knight.
-You know him?

314
00:20:32.263 --> 00:20:33.697
Yeah. we've already kicked his ass.

315
00:20:33.973 --> 00:20:37.250
And if he shows up again. we have a
vanquishing potion ready and waiting.

316
00:20:37.602 --> 00:20:39.798
-What's in it?
-It's a mandrake variation

317
00:20:40.063 --> 00:20:42.053
with a little bit of griffin's blood.

318
00:20:42.314 --> 00:20:46.228
Good. if you're going up against
a pustulous knave. which you're not.

319
00:20:46.610 --> 00:20:50.126
If you want to fight the Dark Knight
with magic. this is what you need.

320
00:20:51.782 --> 00:20:53.455
I thought you said
you weren't a sorcerer.

321
00:20:53.742 --> 00:20:57.497
I picked up a few things along the way.
The Dark Knight is no trifle.

322
00:20:57.829 --> 00:20:59.786
You'll have to hit him
with everything you have.

323
00:21:00.082 --> 00:21:02.358
I've never even heard of half
of these ingredients.

324
00:21:02.668 --> 00:21:04.545
Looks like he picked up
quite a bit.

325
00:21:06.588 --> 00:21:08.306
What do you think?

326
00:21:10.717 --> 00:21:13.027
-Can't get a read on him.
-Your distrust is expected.

327
00:21:13.303 --> 00:21:15.817
but don't let it blind you.
If I haven't taught Piper

328
00:21:16.098 --> 00:21:19.454
how to master the sword
before the Dark Knight returns.

329
00:21:19.810 --> 00:21:21.528
your survival depends on that potion.

330
00:21:22.396 --> 00:21:24.706
Okay. so where are we supposed
to get the ingredients?

331
00:21:25.023 --> 00:21:29.381
I think I know a place. Leave it to me.
your trusty assistant.

332
00:21:30.153 --> 00:21:32.986
All right. I guess I will go check
with the other elders

333
00:21:33.282 --> 00:21:35.398
and see what they know.

334
00:21:35.701 --> 00:21:37.419
You want me to take Wyatt?

335
00:21:38.829 --> 00:21:40.581
-Piper.
-Hmm?

336
00:21:40.872 --> 00:21:42.385
Do you want me to take
Wyatt with me?

337
00:21:42.666 --> 00:21:44.020
Oh. yeah. Sure.

338
00:21:47.212 --> 00:21:48.646
I'll be fine.

339
00:21:51.967 --> 00:21:53.116
-En garde!
-Aah!

340
00:21:56.888 --> 00:22:00.404
Not bad.
Better than Arthur's first time.

341
00:22:00.767 --> 00:22:04.317
-Really?
-Now. I'm gonna come in low.

342
00:22:06.064 --> 00:22:10.057
Believe in Excalibur.
Just let it flow through you.

343
00:22:15.698 --> 00:22:18.167
-These are your best?
-The highest quality.

344
00:22:18.451 --> 00:22:20.840
-They'll get the job done.
-They'd better.

345
00:22:21.120 --> 00:22:23.794
If they don't. it's not me
they'll have to answer to.

346
00:22:24.081 --> 00:22:26.675
-I thought you were...
-I serve a greater power.

347
00:22:27.001 --> 00:22:28.355
Whose?

348
00:22:28.586 --> 00:22:30.304
[DOOR CLOSES]

349
00:22:32.089 --> 00:22:33.488
We've got a problem.

350
00:22:35.343 --> 00:22:36.697
DWARF:
Hey!

351
00:22:40.890 --> 00:22:44.485
Well. Should have figured
you'd be after the sword.

352
00:22:44.810 --> 00:22:47.370
-Tell him.
-Kiss my grumpy ass.

353
00:22:48.773 --> 00:22:49.773
Tell him.

354
00:22:51.692 --> 00:22:53.091
You're too late.

355
00:22:53.319 --> 00:22:56.835
Piper Halliwell has Excalibur.
And she's being trained how to use it.

356
00:22:57.156 --> 00:22:59.989
By who? Who's training her?

357
00:23:01.494 --> 00:23:03.007
[DEMON GROANS]

358
00:23:04.789 --> 00:23:09.784
-Does this change anything?
-It changes everything.

359
00:23:17.927 --> 00:23:22.398
I think we got everything you need.
Plant roots. fungi. herbs.

360
00:23:22.765 --> 00:23:25.757
-creature parts. insects.
-Creature parts?

361
00:23:26.060 --> 00:23:27.494
RICHARD:
Fairy wings.

362
00:23:27.728 --> 00:23:29.366
Wait. fairy wings?

363
00:23:29.605 --> 00:23:31.960
Well. I didn't kill them
if that's what you're wondering.

364
00:23:32.233 --> 00:23:33.792
-Then how'd you get them?
-Uh. Phoebe.

365
00:23:33.984 --> 00:23:36.021
-What? Fair question.
-Actually. I'm not sure.

366
00:23:36.278 --> 00:23:39.509
My family's been stockpiling this stuff
for years because of the feud.

367
00:23:39.864 --> 00:23:41.775
Yeah. but the feud's over. right?

368
00:23:42.075 --> 00:23:43.748
Hey. you know.
I think we're gonna need

369
00:23:43.994 --> 00:23:46.747
a mortar and pestle for the potion.
do you have one?

370
00:23:47.038 --> 00:23:48.233
Yeah.

371
00:23:50.250 --> 00:23:51.968
What are you doing?

372
00:23:52.210 --> 00:23:53.803
-What?
-You don't have to treat him

373
00:23:54.045 --> 00:23:57.356
-like he's evil.
-Paige. I'm just reacting to what I see.

374
00:23:57.716 --> 00:24:01.027
I mean. how many guys do you
know that stockpile gremlin ears?

375
00:24:01.344 --> 00:24:03.384
Okay. first your not-so-subtle column.
and now this.

376
00:24:03.638 --> 00:24:05.709
Why don't you come out
and admit it? You hate him.

377
00:24:06.016 --> 00:24:08.895
Paige. I don't hate him.
I'm just worried.

378
00:24:09.227 --> 00:24:11.104
Well. don't worry.
I know what I'm doing.

379
00:24:11.354 --> 00:24:13.914
Okay. so are you telling me
that it doesn't bother you at all

380
00:24:14.190 --> 00:24:16.420
that he's using magic again?
Or that he has this...?

381
00:24:16.693 --> 00:24:19.162
This room hidden?

382
00:24:19.487 --> 00:24:23.162
What part of "this is not
your business" are you not getting?

383
00:24:23.491 --> 00:24:26.244
Oh. Paige. I am worried about you.

384
00:24:26.536 --> 00:24:29.216
Okay. just like you were worried
about me when I was dating a demon.

385
00:24:29.456 --> 00:24:33.086
-Richard is not a demon.
-No. I know he's not a demon. Paige.

386
00:24:33.418 --> 00:24:35.409
But he has a dark side
and powerful magic.

387
00:24:35.670 --> 00:24:37.308
And that's a very dangerous
combination.

388
00:24:37.547 --> 00:24:40.824
I... I'm worried about you. okay?
I'm sorry.

389
00:24:44.596 --> 00:24:48.032
-Here.
-Thanks.

390
00:24:49.684 --> 00:24:51.516
Everything all right?

391
00:24:52.020 --> 00:24:53.215
[SIGHS]

392
00:24:54.981 --> 00:24:56.938
Let's just get this over with.

393
00:25:01.654 --> 00:25:03.247
[GRUNTING]

394
00:25:16.877 --> 00:25:19.266
-You're a quick study.
-You're a good teacher.

395
00:25:20.381 --> 00:25:23.453
So you feel the sword's power?

396
00:25:23.801 --> 00:25:25.872
-Yes.
-How's it feel?

397
00:25:27.054 --> 00:25:28.089
Not bad.

398
00:25:30.140 --> 00:25:32.370
You and Excalibur are becoming one.

399
00:25:33.644 --> 00:25:36.318
Soon. nothing will matter.

400
00:25:36.647 --> 00:25:39.366
Nothing except the desire to rule.

401
00:25:50.494 --> 00:25:51.564
You.

402
00:25:51.829 --> 00:25:54.503
I was wondering when you'd show up.
Take him!

403
00:26:03.048 --> 00:26:04.641
[YELLING]

404
00:26:07.678 --> 00:26:11.353
-"Wereboar tusk. one pinch."
-Okay.

405
00:26:12.016 --> 00:26:13.370
PAIGE:
Nymph hair. one lock.

406
00:26:13.601 --> 00:26:16.514
Oh. I hope this isn't
from someone we know.

407
00:26:17.146 --> 00:26:20.537
Wraith essence. three drops.

408
00:26:21.442 --> 00:26:25.150
-One. two. three.
-And black poppy.

409
00:26:25.486 --> 00:26:28.080
-"one level teaspoon."
-I've never even heard of black...

410
00:26:28.406 --> 00:26:29.635
No!

411
00:26:32.285 --> 00:26:34.276
Phoebe. you okay?

412
00:26:36.706 --> 00:26:40.381
-Richard.
-Wait. watch.

413
00:26:42.337 --> 00:26:45.170
Don't ever mix wraith essence
and black poppy.

414
00:26:46.090 --> 00:26:48.923
-Ever.
-Why would Mordaunt do this?

415
00:26:49.260 --> 00:26:50.694
Because he wants you dead.

416
00:26:56.684 --> 00:26:58.004
[SCREAMS]

417
00:27:15.620 --> 00:27:17.770
-I thought we made a deal.
-I don't need you

418
00:27:18.039 --> 00:27:19.757
to get the sword anymore.

419
00:27:22.460 --> 00:27:24.258
I've got her.

420
00:27:29.759 --> 00:27:31.636
Your assimilation is complete.

421
00:27:32.387 --> 00:27:34.503
You are now one with Excalibur.

422
00:27:34.806 --> 00:27:36.399
Now what?

423
00:27:38.518 --> 00:27:41.192
-It's just us.
-He's not what you think he is.

424
00:27:41.479 --> 00:27:43.709
-He tried to kill us.
-He wants the sword.

425
00:27:44.274 --> 00:27:45.548
But the sword chose me.

426
00:27:45.817 --> 00:27:49.014
No. he's just using you. he wants
the power of the sword for himself.

427
00:27:49.362 --> 00:27:51.921
You're not meant
to control the sword.

428
00:27:52.281 --> 00:27:53.715
But I do control it.

429
00:27:56.285 --> 00:27:57.958
And you don't think I can.

430
00:28:00.247 --> 00:28:01.476
Perhaps we should leave.

431
00:28:03.041 --> 00:28:05.430
-Paige. Paige. Paige. Paige.
-Excalibur!

432
00:28:10.007 --> 00:28:11.918
Don't do that again.

433
00:28:13.677 --> 00:28:15.748
It appears your queen has spoken.

434
00:28:19.766 --> 00:28:22.884
Her Majesty has left the building.

435
00:28:23.228 --> 00:28:25.060
Or Her Madness.

436
00:28:31.945 --> 00:28:34.255
Doesn't look like much of a kingdom.

437
00:28:34.740 --> 00:28:37.459
Well. this is just where it begins.

438
00:28:37.743 --> 00:28:40.098
where you form your inner circle.

439
00:28:40.579 --> 00:28:43.492
Let me guess.
the Knights of the Round Table?

440
00:28:43.790 --> 00:28:45.906
The knights of your Round Table.

441
00:28:46.543 --> 00:28:50.776
You're on a new path now.
a new destiny.

442
00:28:51.757 --> 00:28:55.387
That's good because I was
getting a little bored of the old one.

443
00:28:55.719 --> 00:28:57.835
A world of adventure awaits you.

444
00:28:58.096 --> 00:29:01.407
Warfare. conquest.

445
00:29:01.725 --> 00:29:03.636
Camelot.

446
00:29:04.353 --> 00:29:09.063
-And what exactly is Camelot?
-Whatever you want it to be.

447
00:29:09.483 --> 00:29:11.679
It's your kingdom to make.

448
00:29:11.944 --> 00:29:13.901
Could you be a little more specific?

449
00:29:14.947 --> 00:29:18.985
There will be no one above you.
no one to challenge you.

450
00:29:19.367 --> 00:29:22.246
You will have free rein
to reshape the way things are.

451
00:29:22.578 --> 00:29:25.889
to create a world of your dreams.

452
00:29:26.874 --> 00:29:29.946
All will bow down before you.

453
00:29:30.294 --> 00:29:32.604
All will serve your every desire.

454
00:29:33.256 --> 00:29:37.045
-Including you?
-Especially me. my queen.

455
00:29:56.362 --> 00:29:58.080
What is it?

456
00:30:00.241 --> 00:30:02.118
Well. we must...

457
00:30:02.702 --> 00:30:04.420
...build your kingdom first.

458
00:30:04.662 --> 00:30:08.815
And to do that. we need to fill
your Round Table with knights.

459
00:30:10.376 --> 00:30:12.845
-Very well. I have a few ideas.
-No.

460
00:30:14.672 --> 00:30:18.188
Let me be your counsel.
I know best who will serve you well.

461
00:30:18.509 --> 00:30:20.022
But they will not come easily.

462
00:30:20.303 --> 00:30:23.694
You must challenge them
on fields of battle.

463
00:30:24.056 --> 00:30:25.774
Force them to join you.

464
00:30:34.483 --> 00:30:36.838
I think I can do that.

465
00:30:43.909 --> 00:30:47.186
-Anything?
-Nope. can't find Piper anywhere.

466
00:30:47.495 --> 00:30:50.055
Well. Keep looking. she's bound
to show up somewhere.

467
00:30:50.332 --> 00:30:51.925
-Yeah. to do what?
-I don't know.

468
00:30:52.167 --> 00:30:55.159
I don't understand. If she wasn't
supposed to pull the sword out.

469
00:30:55.462 --> 00:30:57.822
-then why was she able to?
-According to the other elders.

470
00:30:58.048 --> 00:31:01.166
she was only meant to pass it on
to whomever it was really meant for.

471
00:31:01.509 --> 00:31:04.786
So she's not the new King Arthur.
but she is the new Lady of the Lake?

472
00:31:05.138 --> 00:31:07.971
-Basically. yeah.
-Well. why is it turning her evil?

473
00:31:08.308 --> 00:31:10.822
Because only the ultimate power
on Earth can handle Excalibur.

474
00:31:11.102 --> 00:31:12.622
That's why the lady
stayed in the lake.

475
00:31:12.854 --> 00:31:14.572
to insulate herself
from the sword's power.

476
00:31:14.856 --> 00:31:17.530
Okay. so we should find Piper
and then drown her.

477
00:31:18.944 --> 00:31:20.981
-Oh. I'm just kidding. Leo.
-It's no joke.

478
00:31:21.238 --> 00:31:24.230
It's the only way to keep the power
from consuming her. destroying her.

479
00:31:25.742 --> 00:31:27.858
Still. what does Mordaunt
want with Piper?

480
00:31:28.119 --> 00:31:31.316
I mean. he's tricky. but he's hardly
the ultimate power on Earth.

481
00:31:31.665 --> 00:31:33.497
But he can use Piper
to become that power.

482
00:31:36.503 --> 00:31:38.141
Guess who just surfaced.

483
00:31:46.179 --> 00:31:49.217
-Should I kill him?
-You're the queen.

484
00:31:49.724 --> 00:31:52.398
I need one more knight
to sit at my Round Table.

485
00:31:52.686 --> 00:31:56.441
-Care to join me?
-Join you? Which side are you on?

486
00:31:56.773 --> 00:31:59.925
All we're interested in
is the greatest power.

487
00:32:00.235 --> 00:32:01.589
Become one of us.

488
00:32:03.363 --> 00:32:05.479
-What he said.
-What do I get out of it?

489
00:32:05.740 --> 00:32:07.696
You? You get to live.

490
00:32:09.368 --> 00:32:11.439
-Piper!
-I should have known it was a trap!

491
00:32:12.538 --> 00:32:16.247
-You stay put. You. I warned you.
-Sorry. Your Majesty.

492
00:32:18.168 --> 00:32:20.444
Paige. now. orb her.

493
00:32:27.636 --> 00:32:31.948
Impressive. huh?
Now. make your queen proud.

494
00:32:34.560 --> 00:32:35.789
[ELECTRICITY CRACKLES]

495
00:32:39.607 --> 00:32:41.047
-What just happened?
-I don't know.

496
00:32:41.275 --> 00:32:42.834
but I don't think it's good.

497
00:32:48.240 --> 00:32:49.878
Leo!

498
00:32:54.955 --> 00:32:56.184
PIPER:
Welcome.

499
00:32:56.415 --> 00:32:58.884
I assume you're all wondering
why you've been gathered here.

500
00:32:59.168 --> 00:33:03.082
But don't worry. if I wanted to kill you.
I would have done so already.

501
00:33:03.422 --> 00:33:07.336
You are the chosen few
who will help chart a new world order.

502
00:33:07.676 --> 00:33:09.508
united under me.

503
00:33:09.803 --> 00:33:12.761
Excuse me. Your Majesty.
we're getting ahead of ourselves.

504
00:33:13.057 --> 00:33:16.766
-Are we?
-The small matter of the loyalty oath.

505
00:33:17.645 --> 00:33:21.115
Oh. yeah. That's right. Uh...

506
00:33:21.440 --> 00:33:24.432
-Administer that oath.
-Yes. Your Majesty.

507
00:33:24.735 --> 00:33:27.853
If you will all put
your left hand...

508
00:33:28.197 --> 00:33:29.426
[DEMON GROWLS]

509
00:33:29.698 --> 00:33:31.371
...or claw

510
00:33:31.617 --> 00:33:34.290
on one of the five points
of the pentagram in front of you.

511
00:33:40.250 --> 00:33:41.604
[CHANTING
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

512
00:33:45.755 --> 00:33:47.348
[DEMONS GROANING]

513
00:33:47.882 --> 00:33:51.432
Supreme demonic powers.
leave your hosts!

514
00:33:51.970 --> 00:33:55.201
And find a new home
in this willing heart!

515
00:33:56.266 --> 00:33:57.620
What are you doing?

516
00:33:57.976 --> 00:33:59.774
Stop!

517
00:34:13.992 --> 00:34:16.222
You vanquished all my knights. Why?

518
00:34:21.833 --> 00:34:24.905
Fulfilling my centuries-old quest...

519
00:34:25.712 --> 00:34:27.783
...to control Excalibur.

520
00:34:28.464 --> 00:34:31.820
-But it belongs to me.
-No. It doesn't.

521
00:34:33.303 --> 00:34:36.182
It never did. But thanks to you

522
00:34:36.472 --> 00:34:39.191
and the combined powers
of your knights.

523
00:34:39.475 --> 00:34:41.113
now it belongs to me.

524
00:34:42.562 --> 00:34:44.235
I'm the ultimate power.

525
00:34:45.481 --> 00:34:46.801
I don't understand.

526
00:34:48.026 --> 00:34:50.495
It's simply a transfer of power.
that's all.

527
00:34:50.820 --> 00:34:52.731
And now all that remains
to do...

528
00:34:53.406 --> 00:34:56.239
...is to eliminate the true recipient
of Excalibur

529
00:34:56.534 --> 00:35:00.288
before he grows old enough
to fulfill his destiny

530
00:35:00.621 --> 00:35:03.261
as the son of a Charmed One.

531
00:35:04.666 --> 00:35:07.385
You can't hurt him. he's protected.

532
00:35:09.421 --> 00:35:10.820
I couldn't before.

533
00:35:12.549 --> 00:35:14.381
But I can with this.

534
00:35:14.635 --> 00:35:16.114
[PIPER GASPS]

535
00:35:29.524 --> 00:35:30.559
PAIGE:
Ow.

536
00:35:31.235 --> 00:35:32.748
Feeling any better?

537
00:35:32.986 --> 00:35:37.696
No. I'm pretty sure "ow" signifies that
I am not. in fact. feeling any better.

538
00:35:39.368 --> 00:35:43.123
I am getting tired of this whole
soul-separating-from-my-body thing.

539
00:35:43.455 --> 00:35:45.128
It's getting to be a disturbing pattern.

540
00:35:45.415 --> 00:35:48.612
It was pretty close too. Your souls
were getting ready to move on.

541
00:35:48.919 --> 00:35:51.559
-Move on to where exactly?
-Nice try.

542
00:35:53.298 --> 00:35:55.498
I can't believe Piper.
Did you see the look in her eyes?

543
00:35:55.801 --> 00:35:58.793
Hey. at least it looked like
she was having fun for once.

544
00:35:59.721 --> 00:36:01.394
-Find her yet?
-No. nothing.

545
00:36:01.640 --> 00:36:04.837
Keep trying. Just like last time. they
can't do anything until they resurface.

546
00:36:05.143 --> 00:36:07.663
Yeah. unless Mordaunt wants her
to help him rule the underworld.

547
00:36:08.188 --> 00:36:10.577
There's gotta be another way
to get her out of this.

548
00:36:10.899 --> 00:36:13.049
I just wish we knew
who King Arthur is.

549
00:36:13.860 --> 00:36:16.500
-Wait. what do you mean?
-I mean. if we need to separate

550
00:36:16.780 --> 00:36:19.010
Piper from the sword.
what better way than figure out

551
00:36:19.283 --> 00:36:21.035
who she's meant to give it to?

552
00:36:22.411 --> 00:36:23.730
[WYATT COOING]

553
00:36:25.454 --> 00:36:26.933
No.

554
00:36:28.374 --> 00:36:31.412
It's Wyatt. Oh. my God.
It has to be.

555
00:36:32.253 --> 00:36:33.812
[GROANING]

556
00:36:34.088 --> 00:36:35.965
-What's the matter?
-It's Piper. she's hurt.

557
00:36:39.051 --> 00:36:41.406
-Harding Park. Let's go.
-I got Wyatt.

558
00:36:46.851 --> 00:36:50.810
Don't worry. it'll all be over soon.

559
00:36:51.188 --> 00:36:53.748
Once they come for you.
I'll go for him.

560
00:36:57.320 --> 00:36:59.152
PHOEBE: Hurry! Hurry. hurry!
-I am. I am.

561
00:37:04.619 --> 00:37:05.848
Where's Wyatt?

562
00:37:13.336 --> 00:37:15.725
My apologies. King Wyatt.

563
00:37:16.047 --> 00:37:18.926
I guess it just wasn't meant to be.

564
00:37:21.177 --> 00:37:22.656
[TEDDY BEAR SQUEAKS]

565
00:37:28.684 --> 00:37:30.243
What?!

566
00:37:30.603 --> 00:37:33.356
Oh. and that's
his favourite teddy bear.

567
00:37:38.444 --> 00:37:39.673
PIPER:
Hey.

568
00:37:39.904 --> 00:37:41.338
[CLEARS THROAT]

569
00:37:41.989 --> 00:37:44.344
Bet you didn't expect this
when you got up this morning.

570
00:37:44.909 --> 00:37:46.741
But I've still got Excalibur!

571
00:37:47.036 --> 00:37:48.992
-Not for long.
-Go for it. Wyatt.

572
00:38:06.888 --> 00:38:08.447
[SCREAMS]

573
00:38:13.603 --> 00:38:17.483
Okay. sweetie.
that's very. very good.

574
00:38:18.233 --> 00:38:23.262
But we need to put this away
so you don't put an eye out.

575
00:38:23.655 --> 00:38:25.726
At least until you're 18.

576
00:38:35.500 --> 00:38:36.649
How are you?

577
00:38:37.127 --> 00:38:40.438
Oh. fine. Think you can orb this
into the attic?

578
00:38:40.797 --> 00:38:42.390
Absolutely.

579
00:38:45.677 --> 00:38:47.827
Away from any furniture?

580
00:38:48.138 --> 00:38:49.697
[FURNITURE CRASHING]

581
00:38:50.557 --> 00:38:51.592
Sorry.

582
00:38:52.267 --> 00:38:54.178
Don't worry.
I'll just add it to my list.

583
00:39:10.660 --> 00:39:13.971
Hey. I just finished
the last of the filing.

584
00:39:14.538 --> 00:39:17.735
-Great. thanks.
-Is that tomorrow's copy?

585
00:39:18.042 --> 00:39:20.272
Yeah. I'm just doing some
last-minute changes.

586
00:39:20.544 --> 00:39:24.060
This woman right here
is worried that her mother

587
00:39:24.381 --> 00:39:26.258
-might be marrying the wrong guy.
-Really?

588
00:39:26.508 --> 00:39:28.579
Yeah. she thinks he might be
the devil incarnate.

589
00:39:28.886 --> 00:39:31.321
Didn't we vanquish
the devil incarnate?

590
00:39:32.348 --> 00:39:34.180
I told her

591
00:39:34.433 --> 00:39:37.949
that unless she has absolute proof.
she should probably butt out

592
00:39:38.270 --> 00:39:40.102
and let her sister live her own life.

593
00:39:40.397 --> 00:39:43.594
-I thought this was about a mother.
-Yeah. well. you know what I mean.

594
00:39:43.943 --> 00:39:45.013
Yeah. I think I do.

595
00:39:45.236 --> 00:39:49.025
It's funny. this is the first job I've
gotten without a magical reason behind it.

596
00:39:49.406 --> 00:39:52.285
Well. there may not have been
a magical reason.

597
00:39:52.576 --> 00:39:53.975
but there was definitely a reason.

598
00:39:55.788 --> 00:39:57.825
I just have to learn
to take my own advice.

599
00:39:58.082 --> 00:40:01.279
Yeah. well. don't stop
worrying about me too much.

600
00:40:01.752 --> 00:40:02.981
Okay.

601
00:40:04.171 --> 00:40:08.324
Hey. sorry to interrupt.
You ready to go?

602
00:40:08.676 --> 00:40:11.429
Yeah. We're going out.
Do you wanna join?

603
00:40:11.762 --> 00:40:14.959
I would love to. actually.

604
00:40:15.266 --> 00:40:17.462
but I'm gonna take a rain check.
It's been a long day.

605
00:40:17.768 --> 00:40:18.768
Okay. Good night.

606
00:40:23.148 --> 00:40:25.025
Hey. Paige.

607
00:40:25.317 --> 00:40:29.675
-you're fired.
-Actually. I quit.

608
00:40:51.551 --> 00:40:53.747
Listen. I want you to promise me

609
00:40:54.012 --> 00:40:56.731
that before we take that thing
out of storage.

610
00:40:57.015 --> 00:40:59.814
that you're gonna play lots
of football and baseball

611
00:41:00.101 --> 00:41:04.413
and have lots of normal toys.
and maybe we'll even get a dog.

612
00:41:04.772 --> 00:41:06.331
What do you think?

613
00:41:07.567 --> 00:41:09.365
How we doing?

614
00:41:09.652 --> 00:41:13.008
Uh. His Highness seems content.

615
00:41:13.907 --> 00:41:16.103
-What about you?
-I'm doing all right.

616
00:41:16.367 --> 00:41:19.166
At least I have my priorities straight
now. I was so busy doing stuff.

617
00:41:19.454 --> 00:41:21.494
and all I really wanted to do
was hang out with him.

618
00:41:22.832 --> 00:41:25.142
Well. you should have more time
for that now.

619
00:41:26.669 --> 00:41:28.421
-I fixed the washer.
-You did?

620
00:41:28.671 --> 00:41:33.666
And the sink and the cable
and the toilet.

621
00:41:34.052 --> 00:41:38.250
Wow. I forgot how handy you were
to have around the house.

622
00:41:42.518 --> 00:41:44.156
Pretty strange. huh?

623
00:41:45.813 --> 00:41:47.372
Kind of scary. actually.

624
00:41:47.649 --> 00:41:49.560
-Why?
-Well. we've seen what he can do

625
00:41:49.817 --> 00:41:53.128
without the sword. I can't begin
to imagine what he could do with it.

626
00:41:54.155 --> 00:41:56.192
Well. whatever it is.
it's meant to be.

627
00:41:56.491 --> 00:41:59.927
Doesn't make it
any less scary. though.

628
00:42:00.245 --> 00:42:03.761
But that's tomorrow's problem.
I'll worry about it then.

629
00:42:04.082 --> 00:42:06.152
Okey-dokey.
